data.name: Chat Log model

data.description: This is the current data has received from the 'output' endpoint. It will print Offline if the bot went offline (internet died, turned off, etc). If It's active, it will print if its loading(starting), or online and print the currentmessage it has stored (does not mean its active)
data.name: Bot Response

data.description: Every non-command chat message and bot message that contains three zero width spaces (Spaces added only when an admin panel command is sent to the bot). It will insert into the database, and this endpoint outputs that. It may be reset at times

response.name: Chat Log model

data.name: Chat Log

data.description: This is the API that the discord bot - Kappa[bot] grabs every two seconds. This is stored in a database and then printed. This is not what the bot outputs, but inputs. Active will be true if the message is not empty, and overwrite means to keep repeating it.  The bot grabs the latest message, compares if it's new then the one in memory. If not it will run command and reset it. If it is different then it changes to the new message, runs it, and disables itself. It will then reset the output to be empty.
data.name: output

data.description: List of per-server prefences, or per-user prefences. Bot fetches it every 10 seconds. Users are registered to database if they chat on a discord server Kappa is running on and they haven't already been registered.
